---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Barbell Bench Press (275lbs)">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Barbell Bench Press (315lbs)</h1>

    <!-- Video Embed -->
    <video class="w-full rounded-lg mb-8" controls>
      <source src="https://sentinel-power-blog-resources.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/Lifting+Videos/315+Bench.MP4" type="video/mp4">
      Your browser does not support the video tag.
    </video>

    <!-- Why I Chose This Exercise -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Why I Chose This Exercise</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">
      The bench press is the ultimate test of upper body pushing strength. It targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps simultaneously, and mastering it is key
      for overall muscle balance and pressing power. Whether you're chasing a bigger 1-rep max or building a thicker chest, the bench press remains an
      essential foundation lift.
    </p>

    <!-- Muscles Worked -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Muscle Groups Targeted</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-400 mb-10">
      <li>Pectoralis Major (Chest)</li>
      <li>Anterior Deltoids (Front Shoulders)</li>
      <li>Triceps Brachii</li>
      <li>Serratus Anterior (Stabilization)</li>
      <li>Core (for tightness and control)</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Back to Training Button -->
    <div class="mt-12">
      <a href="/training" class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-[#1DB954] text-white font-semibold rounded-lg shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition">
        ‚Üê Back to Training
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
